  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">6,000 BREAKFASTS A WEEK FOR CHILDREN IN TANZANIA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following a successful pilot project, we&apos;ll roll out this project to more primary schools on the island of Ukerewe in Lake Victoria (Tanzania).    Schools there have adjacent land which is uncultivated. We set up an environment club, train pupils &amp; selected staff to grow sogum crops for own consumption. Surplus is sold to buy seed, school kit eg chalk, pens &amp; paper.  Porridge is cooked and served by pupils to typically 500 kids 3 days a week encouraging  attendance and improving concentration.</narrative>
  </description>
